author: chris-dollin
msg: Updated reification to distinguish between the "hidden triples" (which
don't appear in the parent graph) and "reification triples" (the
quadlets which might). We can then say that the hidden triples are
disjoint from the parent triples. [As Craig pointed out, this can be
useful, and indeed will be used shortly ...]
Also added some extra tests to AbstractTestReifier, including checking
that the reifier's style is the same as that passed to the graph
creating it, which forced its implementation in the DB reifier.
